    <p style="font-size: 25px;"> The book illustrates how women assert themselves in a male-dominated sphere, challenging traditional gender roles.
        Many stories emphasize resilience and the lengths to which these women go to survive in dangerous circumstances.
        The narratives explore the intricate relationships between women and gangsters, revealing loyalty, betrayal, and power dynamics.
        The theme of seeking a new identity and a life beyond crime resonates throughout the stories. Mafia Queens of Mumbai sheds light on the often-overlooked narratives of women in the underworld, offering a nuanced perspective on their lives, struggles, and triumphs within the context of crime and society.</p>
